I built something like that for one of my clients, its not ideal and developement on modules requier pretty much to use {{ require_css(get_asset_url()) }}

But my final product has one css per page loaded with only stuff thats needed.

All that was needed was to use { include (css file)}

Ale build file dependecies based on what each page needed.

Now this is far from perfect and not really scaleable, but im looking to build more complex version of this in december where i have more time.
